text: So you go to p#,<http://nolop.org|nolop.org> (where the # is the printer number), then you can upload your STL. The website is a slicer, so when you upload, you can check your settings (if you have any overhangs in your print, add support, which you can find in the second setting tab). If your file is in any units besides mm, you’ll need to scale it, which is a button on the top left of the bed screen. There’s also a button there to reorient your part, which you’ll want to do depending on the part (orient in a way that causes the least amount of overhang and has the most amount of material flat on the bed)
